txt.en: Continue talking to the Dumûri warrior, should you wish to return to the Dubarâkh.
'You would like to go then? This is wonderful news. I tire of standing here. Talk to me again when you are ready.'
The Dumûri warrior has led you to the Dubarâkh.
'You would like to go then? This is wonderful news. Guard duty is so dull.'
A Dumûri warrior is offering to escort you back to the Dubarâkh, should you desire it.

'Hashtal-gûr, [placeholder]. I have standing orders to escort you back to the Dubarâkh, if you wish to return there and study the documents. Please let me know if you would like me to take you there.'
'You would like to go then? This is wonderful news. I tire of standing here. Talk to me again when you are ready.
